Project description

Jump Consistent Hash

Python and C implementation of the jump consistent hash algorithm by JohnLamping and Eric Veach[1]. Tested on Python 3.8+.

Install

To install Jump Consistent Hash, simply run this simple command in yourterminal of choice:

$ pip install jump-consistent-hash

The C implementation is optional but is about 10x faster than the pure Pythonimplementation in CPython.

Usage

>>> import jump>>> jump.hash(256, 1024)520

If you want to use a str as a key instead of an int, you can pass itthrough a hash function to compute a real key. Here’s a couple of examplesusing Python 3:

>>> import hashlib>>> int(hashlib.md5(b"127.0.0.1").hexdigest(), 16)325870950296970981340734819828239218902>>> int(hashlib.sha1(b"127.0.0.1").hexdigest(), 16)431133456357828263809343936597625557575256328153>>> import binascii>>> binascii.crc32(b"127.0.0.1") & 0xffffffff3619153832>>> abs(hash("127.0.0.1"))7536019783825143230

Links

[1] http://arxiv.org/pdf/1406.2294v1.pdf
